          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <updateDate>2018-04-27T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Make Sanctuary Cities Pay for the Wall Act of 2018 </b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) to establish a DHS account for the planning, design, and construction of a U.S.-Mexico border barrier.</p> <p>Certain housing, community development, and public works appropriations for sanctuary cities, localities, or states shall be withheld and deposited into such account.</p> <p>DHS: (1) may decline to transfer an alien in its custody to a sanctuary jurisdiction regardless of whether such jurisdiction has issued a writ or warrant, (2) shall not transfer an alien under a final order of removal (or a restatement of an order of removal) to a sanctuary jurisdiction, and (3) shall determine and report to Congress each year which political subdivisions or states are sanctuary jurisdictions. </p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDate>2018-04-27</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        </item>
